{
  "stem": "9995.4",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I had a whole loaf of bread, which some Hungarian girls took away from me.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Not that I didn't fight for it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "When we came to Weimar, that's the famous city because of [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The Ukrainians which were watching us were already by themselves disgusted, and I saw a woman, if they tell-- Germans say that they didn't know what was going on, they lie.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "There were plenty of Germans over there in that depot, and I saw a woman with a girl about my age, and I asked her for a little water.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And she looked at me and turned and walked away.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "She could have given to me.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Then they took us from Weimar-- it's very short distance-- to Buchenwald.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And Buchenwald didn't have a place for us.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So they took us to Bergen-Belsen.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And my mother was in the same transfer, but different one.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I didn't find her.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "She went to Ravensbruck.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "So we didn't meet until well after the war.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "We came to Bergen-Belsen, and there were only crematoria over there for somebody dead, and there was so many people dying that there were piles of dead bodies.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "If you go to Holocaust Museum in Washington, the English made some movies when they took over our camp, so you will see those piles over there because they couldn't manage to-- to burn everybody.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "People were dying like-- you could not be alive when you were healthy longer than three months.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "It just so happened I came at the end of January, and we were freed at April 15 by the English army of General Montgomery.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So although I was so ill, if they would have come two days later, I would have been dead.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And Bergen-Belsen was another nightmare.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "However, I was very lucky.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
